{
  "info": {
    "name": "Hubra Agent API",
    "description": "Agent-callable HTTP surface for Hubra. Read endpoints are public; write endpoints return unsigned Solana transactions for the agent to sign locally with its own keypair, then submit via /broadcast.\n\nNo API key, no sign-up. The agent's keypair is the auth.\n\n**hubra_token gate:** /stake and /unstake responses include a `hubra_token` (HMAC over the unsigned tx's message bytes). /broadcast requires this token so the endpoint can't be used as a free Solana RPC for arbitrary txs. Tokens are valid ~2 minutes.\n\n**Sanctum-routed flows** (sol-liquid-stake, sol-native-stake instant) additionally need `sanctumKind` and `sanctum_order` forwarded from the build response to /broadcast — Sanctum's execute endpoint validates the signed tx against its original order. Native, leveraged, and usdc-earn flows broadcast over plain RPC (`route: \"rpc\"`).\n\n**Leveraged raSOL Max (sol-leveraged-stake) — LIVE.** Deposit takes `amount` in SOL and builds ONE tx: SOL → raSOL (SPL stake-pool DepositSol) → raSOL Max (Voltr depositVault). Unstake takes `amount` = raSOL Max LP to burn (`kind: \"instant\"`) and pays out raSOL via the rasol-max SDK's vault-idle or MarginFi flash-bracket path. To finish to SOL, chain a sol-liquid-stake instant unstake on the resulting raSOL.\n\nThis collection auto-captures `hubra_token`, `transaction`, `stakeAccount`, `sanctumKind`, and `sanctum_order` from successful stake/unstake responses into collection variables (`lastHubraToken`, `lastTransaction`, `lastStakeAccount`, `lastSanctumKind`, `lastSanctumOrder`) — broadcast requests reference them via `{{lastHubraToken}}` etc., so you can run a build then a broadcast back-to-back without manual paste-juggling.\n\nConfigure `baseUrl`, `wallet`, and `stakeAccount` in collection variables before running requests.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "https://hubra.app/api/v1",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Root of the agent API. Production is https://hubra.app/api/v1. For local dev point it at http://localhost:3000/api/v1 (or :3001 if a dev server is already bound to :3000)."
    },
    {
      "key": "wallet",
      "value": "<your-wallet-pubkey>",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Solana wallet pubkey (base58). Replace with the agent's actual wallet before running any flow."
    },
    {
      "key": "stakeAccount",
      "value": "<your-stake-account-pubkey>",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Pubkey of an existing active stake account, used by /unstake and /quote for sol-native-stake. /stake (sol-native-stake) generates a fresh keypair internally and returns the pubkey - that flow doesn't read this variable."
    },
    {
      "key": "lpAmount",
      "value": "0.0195",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "raSOL Max LP to burn on a sol-leveraged-stake /unstake (decimal string, 9 decimals). Read your raSOL Max LP balance on-chain after a leveraged deposit and paste the exact amount here to burn the full position."
    },
    {
      "key": "lastHubraToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-captured from the latest /stake or /unstake response. /broadcast references it via {{lastHubraToken}}."
    },
    {
      "key": "lastTransaction",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-captured base64 unsigned (or partially-signed) tx from the latest /stake or /unstake. NOT directly broadcastable - sign locally first, then paste the signed bytes into /broadcast."
    },
    {
      "key": "lastStakeAccount",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-captured stakeAccount pubkey from the latest sol-native-stake /stake response."
    },
    {
      "key": "lastSanctumKind",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-captured sanctumKind from the latest Sanctum-routed /stake or /unstake response."
    },
    {
      "key": "lastSanctumOrder",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-captured sanctum_order JSON (stringified) from the latest Sanctum-routed /stake or /unstake response. /broadcast Sanctum requests reference it via {{lastSanctumOrder}}."
    }
  ],
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Auto-capture token + tx + Sanctum fields from any 200 response so",
          "// /broadcast and follow-up /unstake calls can reference them by collection variable.",
          "if (!pm.response || pm.response.code !== 200) return;",
          "let body;",
          "try { body = pm.response.json(); } catch (e) { return; }",
          "if (!body || typeof body !== 'object') return;",
          "if (typeof body.hubra_token === 'string') pm.collectionVariables.set('lastHubraToken', body.hubra_token);",
          "if (typeof body.transaction === 'string') pm.collectionVariables.set('lastTransaction', body.transaction);",
          "if (typeof body.stakeAccount === 'string') pm.collectionVariables.set('lastStakeAccount', body.stakeAccount);",
          "if (typeof body.sanctumKind === 'string') pm.collectionVariables.set('lastSanctumKind', body.sanctumKind);",
          "if (body.sanctum_order && typeof body.sanctum_order === 'object') {",
          "  pm.collectionVariables.set('lastSanctumOrder', JSON.stringify(body.sanctum_order));",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Reads",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
